  "description": [
    "Page 44 F D Plan Held Way to Avoid 25 Years of Relief New Deal Officials Support Child Labor Ban and Short Hours Limitation on Working Age In cluded in Three Point Long Range Unemployment Drive Bj United Frew The United States must accept the principles of President Roosevelts suggestions for putting the jobless back to work or pav the huge cost of unemployment relief for the next 25 years New Deal relief officials asserted today Their prediction followed the Pres idents Baltimore speech regarding limitation of the working age and of the work week and prohibition of child labor as aids to solving the unemployment problem The directors of the New Deals 4000000000 work relief program contended that only by following the principles he laid down could the nation withdraw from public relief 3WAY ATTACK While declining to be quoted di rectly they outlined the following program as the only hope of ending relief within a quarter century 1 Adoption of the child labor amendment 2 Full operation of the social se curity program limiting the working age to between 18 to 65 3 Congressional passage of a bill limiting the work week or a revival of that phase"
